         <abstract id="aspace_1e98820688a06d66f9f71bef7aabf871">Correspondence and financial records of William Barrett Pease, son of a New Haven bookseller and Civil War veteran. Most of the letters are from members of his wife's family and relate to Pease's real estate holdings in Brooklyn. A letter (1879 Jul 3) from Samuel Chapman Armstrong, the founder of the Hampton Institute, offers Pease a position at the Institute.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="dts_4029226092827bebd13fb8bddac1e4e61efa6854" source="lcsh">
               <part>Pease, William Barrett, 1844-1903</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
